	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The board may not have actual SRAM on it. I'm not sure but just because a game has WRAM, doesn't mean it's the type of RAM known as SRAM which is used with a battery to always maintain power. So even if a battery power supply were present the RAM might not be the right type. Also if the board wasn't mean for a battery it's going to be messy adding one I would think. Basically I would say find another board for whatever you are doing. RetroZone (retrousb.com) sells a MMC1 repro board that is brand new and will support whatever MMC1 needs you have and you won't destroy any NES games.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

